title: For Sale:  NIB Vector V93 HK33.223 Rifle HK C93 HK93 AT43 Z43
postcontent:
Up for sale is a factory new, unfired, Vector Arms V93 HK33 type rifle, chambered for the popular 5.56mm NATO (.223 Rem) cartridge. This rifle is built from an original HK33 parts kit in Excellent condition, with only the minimal number of 922(r) parts to be legal. It has all of the features of the original military gun, except for of course full-auto. It comes complete with 1 German magazine and military bayonet. 
The HK33 assault rifle was released in the mid 1960s. It was essentially a scaled down German G3 battlerifle, chambered for the then very new .223 Rem cartridge. It prooved just as reliable as the original G3 and the famous MP5, as it used the same roller-delayed locking system. It used many of the same parts and had the same general layout and controls. The HK33 and its variants went on to be adopted by several militaries and were used by many law enforcement agencies all around the world. It was even tested by the US military in Vietnam as the H&R T-223.

title: For Sale:  F.I. Garcia Model D .380 Semi Automatic Pistol
postcontent: A quick history: Garcia tooled up Firearms International to make frames with a couple of small changes (longer grip spur, for one) and struck a deal with Colt, who wanted a small .380 pistol in its line, to produce the Colt "Pony" using FI-made frames and possibly also slides with other parts imported from Star in Spain. These frames had serial numbers starting with 'CPA.' Colt was having one of its internal upheavals and they never got any guns out to speak of - Colt 'Pony' pistols from this run are fairly rare. Garcia/FI had all these frames and the FI Model D was born. This example is in mint condition. Bluing at 99% or better, grips are flawless, and the bore is as new. Includes one magazine, factory box and paperwork. Asking 425.00. Will ship anywhere in the USA(where legal) to your FFL. Buyer pays freight and insurance.

title: For Sale:  Hopkins & Allen falling block 410 gauge
postcontent: Rare 1890's Hopkins & Allen falling block single barrel in 410 gauge.  Serial # 0194 matches on barrel, receiver and trigger.  Falling block action to load and fire; works fine with 2 1/2" modern shells.  Breach end octagonal, rear open sight in dovetail,  and tapers to round at bead sight.  Barrel easily removed from receiver with shown barrel retaining screw.  Barrel stamped: "Hopkins & Allen Arms Co. Norwich, Conn. , USA" and also "410  2.5" for the chamber.  Walnut stock refinished with a solid repair.  Has dings and dents in metal and butt pad is hard but useable.  This may have been a 44-40 barrel that was factory bored for 410 as I can find no other falling block in the 410 bore.  This is an antique that ships direct and that still works as it should with a good pattern and is in good condition in a very hard to find bore.
